First, there's the Safa appeals board for overturning Black Leopards boss David Thidiela's one-year ban from football for his tribal diatribe against referee Victor Hlungwani. The sentence was reduced to a R200,000 fine, from R1m, with R100,000 suspended. Second, is the CAF referee panelist who falsely announced Victor Gomes as the referee for Friday's Afcon final between Senegal and Algeria.